# GenAnh Docker Context

- Workspace root is `/home/chinhanh`; Laravel app root is `app/` and container app root is `/var/www/html`.
- Use Docker for runtime commands. Prefer `docker compose exec app sh -lc 'cd /var/www/html && <command>'` from workspace root.
- Start services with `docker compose up -d` only when needed; do not run `docker compose down -v`, prune, or delete `data/` without explicit user approval.
- Services: `app` (`chinhanh-app`, ports 80/443), `mysql` (host port 33060), `dragonfly` (6380), `memcached` (11212), `imgproxy` (8083).
- Do not run host `php`, `composer`, `artisan`, `npm`, or `pnpm` unless user explicitly asks or container is unavailable.
- Project domain is `https://chinhanh.local`; use it for browser/manual checks and generated absolute app URLs.
- If HTTPS certificate blocks automation, use `curl -k https://chinhanh.local/...` for smoke checks; avoid falling back to `localhost` unless the user asks.
- Use shortest command that proves the change.
- Common checks inside app container: `php artisan test tests/Feature/<file>.php`, `composer test`, `composer lint:check`, `composer types:check`, `npm run build`, `php artisan migrate --pretend`.
- When reporting validation, include commands run, pass/fail result, failing excerpt only, and next smallest fix if obvious.
- After any `php artisan optimize:clear` (or other artisan that recreates files under `storage/` / `bootstrap/cache` as root), always restore ownership for PHP-FPM user `app`:

```bash
docker compose exec app sh -lc 'cd /var/www/html && php artisan optimize:clear && chown -R app:app storage bootstrap/cache'
```

  Never leave `optimize:clear` without the `chown`. Wrong owner causes 500s (e.g. Blade cache `touch()` / `Operation not permitted`).
